<dl id="n53125ad"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53125ad">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53125ad"> 125(ad)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> recognised by eyes, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53125ad"><li>FW 239.05 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kc/lexkc.htm#n53125ad">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kc/l39kc.htm#n53125ad">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53125ad">MS BL 47477-284</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:419 <a name="kad9" href="../../FF/fdra/kda.htm#kcd8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kc/kcd8.htm#n53125ad">Draft: II.1&sect;3.8</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Un conseiller du roi le croisa dans la rue; il regardait les enfants maigres, noircis par le soleil, et, tout &agrave; coup, <mark>il les reconnut &agrave; leurs yeux</mark>. Il interrogea le brahmane: &laquo;D&apos;o&ugrave; tiens-tu ces enfants? &mdash;Seigneur, r&eacute;pondit le brahmane, on me les a donn&eacute;s pour esclaves dans une for&ecirc;t montagneuse; ils ob&eacute;issaient mal, et, maintenant, je cherche &agrave; les vendre.&raquo; <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 157</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: After a long time had passed he returned to Kapilavastou and told those there the story of Visvamitra, a prince who had given away everything that he owned, including his wife and children. The children, however, were safely recovered when a servant of the prince&apos;s father recognised them by their eyes. </mm> </dd></dl>
